[{"location":"#ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","page":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","title":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","title":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","text":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl contains several useful functions to test new group implementations.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","title":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","text":"Modules = [ManifoldGroupTesting]\nOrder = [:type, :function]","category":"page"},{"location":"#ManifoldGroupTesting.check_action_morphism-Union{Tuple{TAD}, Tuple{Manifolds.AbstractGroupAction{TAD}, Any, Any, Any}} where TAD","page":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","title":"ManifoldGroupTesting.check_action_morphism","text":"check_action_morphism(α::GroupAction, χ1, χ2, p)\n\nFor a group action α,\n\nα(χ_1 α(χ_2 p)) = α(m(χ_1 χ_2) p)\n\nwhere for a left action\n\nm(χ_1 χ_2) = χ_1 χ_2\n\nand for a right action\n\nm(χ_1 χ_2) = χ_2 χ_1\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ManifoldGroupTesting.check_adjoint_action-NTuple{5, Any}","page":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","title":"ManifoldGroupTesting.check_adjoint_action","text":"check_adjoint_action(G, grp_rep, alg_rep, χ, ξ)\n\nThe group representation ρ and algebra representation ρ  commute with the adjoint action:\n\nρ(χ) ρ(ξ) ρ(χ)^-1 = ρ(Ad_χ (ξ))\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ManifoldGroupTesting.check_adjoint_action_in_alg-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","title":"ManifoldGroupTesting.check_adjoint_action_in_alg","text":"check_adjoint_action_in_alg(G, χ, ξ)\n\nThe adjoint action of χ on ξ is an element of Alg(G):\n\nAd_χξ  Alg(G)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ManifoldGroupTesting.check_alg_rep-NTuple{4, Any}","page":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","title":"ManifoldGroupTesting.check_alg_rep","text":"check_alg_rep(G, alg_rep, ξ1, ξ2)\n\nThe algebra representation ρ is an algebra morphism.\n\nρ(ξ_1 ξ_2) = ρ(ξ_1) ρ(ξ_2)\n\nwhere the latter is a matrix commutator.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ManifoldGroupTesting.check_apply_diff_group-Union{Tuple{TAD}, Tuple{Manifolds.AbstractGroupAction{TAD}, Any, Any, Any}} where TAD","page":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","title":"ManifoldGroupTesting.check_apply_diff_group","text":"check_apply_diff_group(\n    A::AbstractGroupAction{TAD}, # group action G ⊂ Diff(M)\n    χ, # element of G\n    ξ, # element of Alg(G)\n    p, # element of M\n)\n\nThis should hold for any group action A on any manifold. If you define π_p(χ) = A(χ p) for χ  G and p  M, and define, for ξ  Alg(G),  T_R(χ ξ) = ξχ (the right translation), and T_L(χ ξ) = χξ (the left translation), then we have the identity:\n\nDπ_p(χ) T(χ ξ) = Dπ_A(χp)(1) ξ\n\nwhere, for a left action, T is the right translation, and for a right action, T is the left translation.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ManifoldGroupTesting.check_apply_diff_group_at_id","page":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","title":"ManifoldGroupTesting.check_apply_diff_group_at_id","text":"check_apply_diff_group_at_id(G, side::GroupActionSide)\n\nThe left group operation action on itself α(χ_1)χ_2 is either (left side)\n\nα(χ_1)χ_2 = χ_1 χ_2\n\nor (right side)\n\nα(χ_1)χ_2 = χ_2 χ_1^-1\n\nNow fix χ_2 = 1 (1 is the identity of G) and define f  G  G by f(χ) = α(χ) 1. Since f(1) = 1, its differential at identity is a map Alg(G)  Alg(G). This map is either\n\nId (left side)\n-Id (right side)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#ManifoldGroupTesting.check_apply_morphism_Identity-Tuple{Manifolds.AbstractGroupAction, Any}","page":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","title":"ManifoldGroupTesting.check_apply_morphism_Identity","text":"check_apply_morphism_Identity(α::AbstractGroupAction, p)\n\nFor any action α and p in the manifold, one has\n\nα(1 p) = p\n\nwhere 1 denotes Identity(G) where G is the action group.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ManifoldGroupTesting.check_exp_ad-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","title":"ManifoldGroupTesting.check_exp_ad","text":"Ad and exp commute:\n\nAd_exp(ξ_1)ξ_2 = exp(ad_ξ_1) ξ_2\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ManifoldGroupTesting.check_exp_exp_-NTuple{6, Any}","page":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","title":"ManifoldGroupTesting.check_exp_exp_","text":"check_exp_exp_(G, exp, exp!, χ_, χ, v)\n\nCompare exp and exp!.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ManifoldGroupTesting.check_exp_invariant-NTuple{5, Any}","page":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","title":"ManifoldGroupTesting.check_exp_invariant","text":"check_exp_invariant(G, exp, χ, v, χ_)\n\nThe invariant exponential of  a Lie group fulfils\n\nχ xp_χ(v) = xp_χχ(χ v)\n\nThere is a right version which is not implemented. It would check that\n\nxp_χ(v) χ = xp_χχ(v χ)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ManifoldGroupTesting.check_exp_lie_point-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","title":"ManifoldGroupTesting.check_exp_lie_point","text":"check_exp_lie_point(G, ξ)\n\nThe Lie group exponential sends the vector ξ to an element in the group.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ManifoldGroupTesting.check_exp_log-NTuple{5, Any}","page":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","title":"ManifoldGroupTesting.check_exp_log","text":"check_exp_log(G, exp, log, χ1, χ2)\n\nCheck the identity\n\nexp_χ_1(log_χ_1(χ_2)) = χ_2\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ManifoldGroupTesting.check_grp_rep_Identity-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","title":"ManifoldGroupTesting.check_grp_rep_Identity","text":"check_grp_rep_Identity(G)\n\nThe representation works at the Identity(G) point.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ManifoldGroupTesting.check_grp_rep_compose-NTuple{4, Any}","page":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","title":"ManifoldGroupTesting.check_grp_rep_compose","text":"check_grp_rep_compose(G, ρ, χ1, χ2)\n\nThe group representation ρ commutes with composition.\n\n ρ(χ_1 χ_2) = ρ(χ_1) ρ(χ_2)\n\nwhere the latter is a matrix multiplication.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ManifoldGroupTesting.check_inv_diff-NTuple{4, Any}","page":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","title":"ManifoldGroupTesting.check_inv_diff","text":"check_inv_diff(\n  G, # Group\n  χ, # group element\n  ξ, # Lie algebra element\n  side::Manifolds.GroupActionSide,\n  )\n\nTest the differential of the inverse on a Lie group G. Denote this inverse by I(χ) = χ^-1. If the left and right transports are T_L(χξ) = χξ and T_R(χξ) = ξχ respectively, then\n\nDI(χ) T_L(χξ) = -T_R(χ^-1 ξ)\n\nand\n\nDI(χ) T_R(χξ) = -T_L(χ^-1 ξ)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ManifoldGroupTesting.check_inv_rep-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","title":"ManifoldGroupTesting.check_inv_rep","text":"check_inv_rep(G, grp_rep, χ)\n\nThe group representation ρ commutes with the inverse.\n\nρ(χ)^-1 = ρ(χ^-1)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ManifoldGroupTesting.check_log_exp-NTuple{5, Any}","page":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","title":"ManifoldGroupTesting.check_log_exp","text":"check_log_exp(G, log, exp, χ, v)\n\nCheck the identity\n\nlog_χ(exp_χ(v)) = v\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ManifoldGroupTesting.check_log_log_-NTuple{6, Any}","page":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","title":"ManifoldGroupTesting.check_log_log_","text":"check_log_log_(G, log, log!, v_, χ1, χ2)\n\nCompare log and log!.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ManifoldGroupTesting.check_switch_action_direction-Tuple{Manifolds.AbstractGroupAction, Any, Any}","page":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","title":"ManifoldGroupTesting.check_switch_action_direction","text":"check_switch_action_direction(α::GroupAction, χ, p)\n\nFor any group action α and its dual α obtained by switch_direction one has\n\nα(χp) = α(χ^-1 p)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ManifoldGroupTesting.check_trivial_infinitesimal_action","page":"ManifoldGroupTesting.jl","title":"ManifoldGroupTesting.check_trivial_infinitesimal_action","text":"check_trivial_infinitesimal_action(A::GroupAction, p)\n\nFor an action α and a point p M, consider the function f  G  M defined as f(χ) = α(χ p). The tangent map at identity D = T f(1) is a linear map and sends zero to zero:\n\nD 0 = 0\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"}]
